  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "1b69528c-7a14-471b-98a3-6d5b2bcfaa97",
    "name": "Task Manager",
    "description": "The **Task Manager** collection covers the full lifecycle of a task management REST API running on `localhost:3000`. It is organized into two functional areas:\n\n**Authentication**\n- `POST /auth/register` — Create a new user account.\n- `POST /auth/login` — Authenticate and retrieve an access token.\n\n**Task Management**\n- `POST /tasks` — Create a new task for the authenticated user.\n- `GET /tasks` — Retrieve all tasks belonging to the authenticated user.\n- `GET /tasks/:id` — Fetch a single task by its ID.\n- `PATCH /tasks/:id` — Update an existing task.\n- `DELETE /tasks/:id` — Delete a task.\n- `GET /tasks/:id` *(Get Deleted Task)* — Verify that a deleted task is no longer accessible.\n\n**Error Handling**\n- `GET /tasks/` *(Unauthorized Request)* — Demonstrates the `401 Unauthorized` response returned when a request is made without a valid token.\n\nUse this collection to develop, test, and validate the Task Manager API — from user registration and login through full CRUD operations on tasks, including authentication enforcement.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "54803908",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/54803908-1b69528c-7a14-471b-98a3-6d5b2bcfaa97?source=collection_link"
  },
